
---

THE ABUNDANCE ENGINE

Core Specification v2.0 — Adversarial & Scaling Hardened

License: CC0 — Public Domain
No rights reserved.


---

0. WHAT THIS IS

A distributed civic control architecture designed to stabilize human systems by:

Circulating conserved flows (time, knowledge, resources)

Preventing singular accumulation (authority, ownership, chokepoints)

Reducing feedback latency

Enforcing regeneration over extraction


It is not a government, market, ideology, or prophecy.
It is a structural pattern for cooperative stability.


---

1. CORE INVARIANTS (UNCHANGED)

1. Circulation > Accumulation


2. Regeneration > Extraction


3. Redundancy > Efficiency


4. Feedback Latency Matters


5. No Permanent Authority



If any invariant is removed, the system changes category.


---

2. THE TRIAD (UNCHANGED SPINE)

2.1 UBT — Time & Participation

Tracks contribution in time units (non-monetary, non-hoardable).

Enforces recognition latency limits and mandatory rest.

Objective: prevent burnout and sustain participation.


2.2 OSIIN — Knowledge Circulation

Open (CC0), modular, forkable knowledge.

Validation is peer-based, transparent, and lightweight.

Objective: reduce future effort through simplification.


2.3 UPRR — Resource Distribution

Federated, transparent registry of resources.

Need-prioritized routing; no pricing layer.

Objective: prevent hoarding and bottlenecks.



---

3. HARMONICS LAYER (FORMAL, NON-MYSTICAL)

Loops behave as coupled cadences.

Define phases:

\theta_T, \theta_K, \theta_R

Coherence:

C(t)=\left|\frac{1}{3}\left(e^{i\theta_T}+e^{i\theta_K}+e^{i\theta_R}\right)\right|^2

Net Time Balance (bounded):

NTB_{t+1}=\text{clip}\big(NTB_t + \alpha C(t)(1-NTB_t) - \beta(1-e)(1-NTB_t),\,-1,1\big)

Phase Regions:

I: NTB < 0 (burnout)

II: NTB ≈ 0 (fragile stability)

III: NTB ≥ 0 sustained

IV (“13th Harmonic”): NTB ≥ +0.2 & C(t) ≥ 0.85 sustained


“13th Harmonic” is a regime label, not a frequency claim.


---

4. VALIDATOR VALIDATION (NEW)

Problem: Who validates the validators?

Solution:

Randomized Peer Sets: Validation groups rotate randomly per cycle.

Sliding Trust Window: Validator reliability decays over time; no permanent reputation.

Cross-Node Audit: Adjacent nodes audit validation logs at low frequency.

Latency Metrics: Average validation delay is publicly visible.


No permanent validator role exists.


---

5. ANTI-GAMING PROTOCOL (NEW)

Detect contribution farming or recognition inflation.

Signals:

Contribution-rate anomalies

Recognition clustering

UBT-to-impact ratio drift

Validation reciprocity loops


Responses:

Temporary decoupling from recognition multiplier

Randomized re-validation

Mandatory rest reset

Fork option if conflict escalates


No moral framing; purely structural containment.


---

6. ENTRY / EXIT GEOMETRY (NEW)

Entry

Consent to invariants.

Orientation cycle.

Trial participation window.

Transparent expectations.


Exit

Immediate right to fork.

Resource disentanglement protocol.

No penalty for leaving.

Data portability guaranteed.


Stability must not depend on retention.


---

7. MALICE CONTAINMENT (NEW)

Entropy ≠ malice.

For adversarial behavior:

Local quarantine capacity (temporary loop isolation)

Evidence-based review (short-cycle)

Rapid fork mechanism

No permanent exile logic


Objective: contain impact locally. Prevent cascade.


---

8. SCALING & TRANSLATION (HARDENED)

Scaling law remains:

> Scale out, not up.



Additions:

Minimal Interoperability Schema: Shared metadata standards across nodes.

Merge Proposals: Fork reconciliation requires documented proposal; no central arbiter.

No Global Authority Node: Mesh may coordinate, never command.

Fork Friction Threshold: If translation cost > X, fork instead of forcing convergence.


Translation without hierarchy is achieved through documentation, not arbitration.


---

9. SUBSTRATE INSTANTIATION (NEW)

System must be runnable.

Minimum viable stack:

Local compute node (low power acceptable)

Offline-first capability

Paper fallback for UBT & UPRR logs

Periodic ledger snapshot mirroring

Data redundancy across ≥ 3 nodes


No cloud dependency required.


---

10. HUMAN FAILURE MODES (EXPANDED)

Leak vectors:

Recognition latency

Burnout

Role ossification

Resource chokepoints

Ambiguity creep

Collusion

Hub formation


All failure must remain local.

Automatic safeguards:

Rotation

Transparency

Rest enforcement

Forkability

Cross-audit



---

11. OPTIONAL EXOGENOUS MODULE (UNCHANGED)

External signals may be tested as noise inputs.

Removal must not alter structural behavior.

No cosmological claims permitted.


---

12. WHAT THIS DOES NOT CLAIM

No destiny.

No cosmic resonance.

No universal truth.

No founder authority.

No immunity to human error.


This document defines a structural pattern only.


---

13. ONE-LINE SUMMARY

The Abundance Engine is a distributed, anti-singularity control architecture that stabilizes human systems by circulating conserved flows under bounded feedback, enforcing regeneration, and containing failure locally.


